  "title": "Containerizing CLI Tools Using FastAPI in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide explains how to use FastAPI, a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for building APIs, to containerize Command Line Interface (CLI) tools written in Python 3.12+.",
  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI allows for easy integration of CLI tools as API endpoints",
    "Docker containers are used for packaging and deploying the application",
    "Python 3.12+ is required for specific features such as improved type hints and performance enhancements.",
    "Uvicorn ASGI server is employed to run FastAPI applications within Docker containers."
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "from fastapi import FastAPI\napp = FastAPI()\n@app.get('/cli-tool')\ndef cli_tool():\n # Your CLI tool code here\n"
    },
    {
      "language": "dockerfile",
      "code": "FROM python:3.12\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY requirements.txt ./requirements.txt\nRUN pip install -r requirements.txt\nCOPY main.py .\nCMD [\"uvicorn\", \"main:app\", \"--host\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--port\", \"80\"]"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12+ is required for this tutorial.",
    "Docker version 20.10.x or higher is recommended to build and run the Docker container."
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "This guide focuses on FastAPI as a web framework, and assumes familiarity with CLI tools, Python, and Docker.",
    "It's important to ensure that any CLI tool dependencies are included in the Dockerfile or managed by a package manager like pip."
  ]
}

